rong&gt;</ph>HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>Software<ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>Microsoft<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>AppV<ph id=\"ph5\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>Client<ph id=\"ph6\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>Integration<ph id=\"ph7\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>.","pos":[11175,11381]},{"content":"Create the DWORD value <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>PreserveUserIntegrationsOnLogin<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> with a value of <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>1<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>.","pos":[11398,11505]},{"content":"Restart the App-V client service or restart the computer running the App-V Client.","pos":[11522,11604]},{"content":"If you have not pre-configured (<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Add-AppvClientPackage<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>) a specific package and this setting is not configured, the App-V Client will de-integrate<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt> the persisted user integrations, then re-integrate<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.","pos":[11645,11860]},{"content":"For every package that meets the above conditions, effectively twice the work will be done during publishing/refresh.","pos":[11868,11985]},{"content":"If you don’t plan to pre-configure every available user package in the base image, use this setting.","pos":[12015,12115]},{"content":"MaxConcurrentPublishingRefresh","pos":[12168,12198]},{"content":"Configure in the Registry under <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Software<ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>Microsoft<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>AppV<ph id=\"ph5\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Client<ph id=\"ph6\">&lt;/strong&gt; \\ &lt;strong&gt;</ph>Publishing<ph id=\"ph7\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>.","pos":[12215,12418]},{"content":"Create the DWORD value <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>MaxConcurrentPublishingrefresh<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> with the desired maximum number of concurrent publishing refreshes.","pos":[12435,12573]},{"content":"The App-V client service and computer do not need to be restarted.","pos":[12590,12656]},{"content":"This setting determines the number of users that can perform a publishing refresh/sync at the same time.","pos":[12697,12801]},{"content":"The default setting is no limit.","pos":[12802,12834]},{"content":"Limiting the number of concurrent publishing refreshes prevents excessive CPU usage that could impact computer performance.","pos":[12864,12987]},{"content":"This limit is recommended in an RDS environment, where multiple users can log in to the same computer at the same time and perform a publishing refresh sync.","pos":[12988,13145]},{"content":"If the concurrent publishing refresh threshold is reached, the time required to publish new applications and make them available to end users after they log in could take an indeterminate amount of time.","pos":[13153,13356]},{"content":"Configure UE-V solution for App-V Approach","pos":[13398,13440]},{"content":"We recommend using Microsoft User Experience Virtualization (UE-V) to capture and centralize application settings and Windows operating system settings for a specific user.","pos":[13442,13614]},{"content":"These settings are then applied to the different computers that are accessed by the user, including desktop computers, laptop computers, and virtual desktop infrastructure (VDI) sessions.","pos":[13615,13802]},{"content":"UE-V is optimized for RDS and VDI scenarios.","pos":[13803,13847]},{"pos":[13849,13984],"content":"For more information see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Getting Started With User Experience Virtualization 2.0<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn458926.aspx)</ept>"},{"content":"In essence all that is required is to install the UE-V client and download the following Microsoft authored App-V settings template from the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft User Experience Virtualization (UE-V) template gallery<ept id=\"p1\">](http://gallery.technet.microsoft.com/Authored-UE-V-Settings-bb442a33)</ept>.","pos":[13986,14264]},{"content":"Register the template.","pos":[14265,14287]},{"content":"For more information around UE-V templates see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>The UE-V specific resource for acquiring and registering the template<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn458926.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[14288,14460]},{"content":"Note","pos":[14464,14468]},{"content":"Without performing an additional configuration step, the Microsoft User Environment Virtualization (UE-V) will not be able to synchronize the Start menu shortcuts (.lnk files) on the target computer.","pos":[14473,14672]},{"content":"The .lnk file type is excluded by default.","pos":[14673,14715]},{"content":"UE-V will only support removing the .lnk file type from the exclusion list in the RDS and VDI scenarios, where every user’s device will have the same set of applications installed to the same location and every .lnk file is valid for all the users’ devices.","pos":[14717,14974]},{"content":"For example, UE-V would not currently support the following 2 scenarios, because the net result will be that the shortcut will be valid on one but not all devices.","pos":[14975,15138]},{"content":"If a user has an application installed on one device with .lnk files enabled and the same native application installed on another device to a different installation root with .lnk files enabled.","pos":[15144,15338]},{"content":"If a user has an application installed on one device but not another with .lnk files enabled.","pos":[15344,15437]},{"content":"Important","pos":[15444,15453]},{"content":"This topic describes how to change the Windows registry by using Registry Editor.","pos":[15458,15539]},{"content":"If you change the Windows registry incorrectly, you can cause serious problems that might require you to reinstall Windows.","pos":[15540,15663]},