":"Attaching and detaching a user profile disk (UPD) or similar technology that contains the user integrations.","pos":[16832,16940]},{"pos":[16946,17059],"content":"**Note**  \nApp-V is supported when using UPD only when the entire profile is stored on the user profile disk.","leadings":["","    "],"nodes":[{"content":"Note","pos":[2,6]},{"content":"App-V is supported when using UPD only when the entire profile is stored on the user profile disk.","pos":[11,109]}]},{"content":"App-V packages are not supported when using UPD with selected folders stored in the user profile disk.","pos":[17065,17167]},{"content":"The Copy on Write driver does not handle UPD selected folders.","pos":[17168,17230]},{"content":"Capturing changes to the locations, which constitute the user integrations, prior to session logoff.","pos":[17243,17343]},{"content":"With App-V 5.1 when you add a publishing server (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add-AppvPublishingServer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>) you can configure synchronization, for example refresh during log on and/or after a specified refresh interval.","pos":[17345,17535]},{"content":"In both cases a scheduled task is created.","pos":[17536,17578]},{"content":"In previous versions of App-V 5.1, both scheduled tasks were configured using a VBScript that would initiate the user and global refresh.","pos":[17580,17717]},{"content":"With Hotfix Package 4 for Application Virtualization 5.0 SP2 the user refresh on log on was initiated by <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SyncAppvPublishingServer.exe<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[17718,17856]},{"content":"This change was introduced to provide UPM solutions a trigger process.","pos":[17857,17927]},{"content":"This process delays the publish /refresh to allow the UPM solution to apply the user integrations.","pos":[17928,18026]},{"content":"It will exit once the publishing/refresh is complete.","pos":[18027,18080]},{"content":"User Integrations","pos":[18084,18101]},{"content":"Registry – HKEY<ph id=\"ph1\">\\_</ph>C